Git Commands:
1. Staging files are ready to commit.
 git add . or git add -A or git add "file name"-to track particular files.
 
2. Initialize Git repo
 git init
 
3. Set basic user configuration variables
 git config --global user.name <your_name>
git config --global user.email <your_email_id>

4. Repository Status
 git status
 
5. Commit 
git commit -m "commit_message"
//if you dont give "-m" and the commit message, it will open an editor to type the commit message there
or
git commit -a -m "commit_message"

6. Append a commit
git commit --amend -m "updated commit message" //to edit only the commit message of the last commit
or
git commit --amend --no-edit //to modify files and include in last commit

7. Log of the commits and show full change history
git log

8. Show differences in various commits
git diff

Branches
9. Create a new branch
git branch <new_branch_name>

10. Checkout to another branch
git checkout <that new branch name>
or
git checkout -b <new_branch_name> //to create a new branch and automatically switch to it

11.Delete a branch
git branch -d <branch name>
or
git branch -D <branch name> //to force delete a branch

12. List of all the branches
git branch

13. Merge two branches
//checkout to the branch you want to merge to
git merge <branch you want to merge>

14. Abort a merge
git merge --abort

15. List the changes dates and authors of the file
 git blame "file"
 
16. Fetch the latest changes from origin and merge
 git pull
 
17. Fetch the latest changes from origin and rebase
 git pull --rebase
 
18. push local changes to the origin
 git push
 
19. download from existing repository
 git clone
 
20. get the latest change in the origin(no merge)
 git fetch
 
21. Tag the current commit
 git tag
 
22. Applying some commit from one branch to another
 git cherry-pick
 
23. When you pull their changes into your local repository, you’ll notice that there is a conflict. This happens because Git no idea whether your friend’s version is the updated version or your version is the updated version. This is what we call a Git conflict.- Git conflict

24.Clone via HTTPS Clone with Git or checkout with SVN using the repository’s web address. Learn more about clone URLs Download ZIP. Raw automation.yml This file contains bidirectional Unicode text that may be interpreted or compiled differently than what appears below. To review, open the file in an editor that reveals hidden Unicode characters-git automation.yml

25. The git stashcommand takes your uncommitted changes (both staged and unstaged), saves them away for later use, and then reverts them from your working copy
 git stash

